Samsung has opened pre-orders for its 85-inch 8K QLED TV in the US. The 85-inch Q900 will start shipping on 28 October 2018, and is priced at $14,999. A direct conversion to rand pegs the TV at R220,000. The TV features an 8K resolution (7,680 x 4,320), 8K AI upscaling, and Q HDR 8K. HDMI, USB, and Ethernet ports are also included, along with Wi-Fi connectivity. “Samsung QLED 8K Q900’s exceptional depth, detail, and high resolution transports you into a new dimension of groundbreaking picture quality,” said Samsung.